                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        <p>
                          Notice that <m>J</m> is a triangular matrix with <m>0</m>'s along the diagonal. Thus <m>\cp_J(x)=x^{2n}</m>, the product of the diagonal entries of the matrix <m>J-xI</m>.
