              <exercise>
                <title></title>
                
                
                <statement>
                  <p>
                    Consider the following matrix over <m>\Q</m>: <me>\begin{bmatrix}-1&amp;0&amp;0&amp;0\\0&amp;-1&amp;0&amp;0\\-2&amp;-2&amp;0&amp;1\\-2&amp;0&amp;-1&amp;-2\end{bmatrix}</me> 

                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        <p>
                          Show that the characteristic and minimal polynomials of <m>A</m> are, respectively, <m>(x + 1)^4</m> and <m>(x + 1)^3</m>. 
                        </p>
                      </li>

                      <li>
                        <p>
                          Find the rational canonical form <m>R</m> of <m>A</m> and the Jordan canonical form <m>J</m> of <m>A</m>. 
                        </p>
                      </li>

                      <li>
                        <p>
                          Find an invertible matrix <m>P</m> such that <m>P\inv AP = J</m>.
                        </p>
                      </li>
