              <exercise>
                <title></title>
                
                
                <statement>
                  <p>
                    Suppose that <m>F \sse L</m> is a finite Galois extension with Galois group <m>G</m>, and that <m>\a \in L</m>. Prove that <m>L = F (\a)</m> if and only if the images of <m>\a</m> under elements of <m>G</m> are distinct.
                  </p>
